fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-009",
  description: "Port the anthill-todo CLI from the native Rust monolith to anthill. Umbrella WI tracked in phases: 1a bundle scaffolding (done), 1b parse_argv over OperationSpec (done), phase 2 read-only commands list/show/status/graph/next via KB.execute (done), phase 3 mutating commands claim/deliver/verify/update/delete/add-dependency/remove-dependency landed as bundle logic with in-place source-span retract via IndexedFileStore (WI-187, delivered) — verified by anthill-todo/tests/cmd_*_test.rs. Current state: the anthill bundle (rustland/anthill-todo/anthill/{main.anthill ~1636 LOC, store.anthill}) implements the subcommand catalogue but is reachable ONLY via the hidden `--anthill` flag; src/main.rs (~2015 LOC) still dispatches every default-path subcommand to native Rust run_* functions + text-surgery. Closing bar (acceptance is just ToolPasses(cargo-test), which is weaker than the goal): (1) invoking `anthill-todo <subcommand>` with NO --anthill flag routes through the anthill bundle for all subcommands; (2) src/main.rs is reduced to a thin shim (bootstrap/KB-load/entry-dispatch only — no run_* business logic, no update_*_in_source text surgery); (3) cargo-test green including an integration test asserting the default path is byte-identical to the legacy output. Remaining gate is essentially just the CUTOVER: drop the --anthill gate, route default dispatch through the bundle, thin src/main.rs to a shim (no run_* / no update_*_in_source), add the default-path parity test. Perf already addressed (WI-183 Verified — Map[K,V] adoption: list 4.5x, graph 38x faster, byte-identical to legacy; residual ~5x gap vs native is a known, acceptable tradeoff). Source-span retract done (WI-187). Optional cleanup: WI-188 .copy / WI-189 staging brackets for terser mutators. Do NOT close until the default dispatch no longer touches native run_* code.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-051", "WI-159", "WI-164", "WI-175", "WI-176"],
  status: Claimed(agent: "claude", since: "2026-05-05T16:55:47Z"))

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-010",
  description: "Implement type-unification helpers as anthill rules so type_of(?env, ?occ, ?type) rules (WI-011) can reason about types declaratively. Three relations to define: (a) subtype(?sub, ?sup) / assignable(?from, ?to) covering primitive subtyping and structural compatibility; (b) resolve_sort_alias(?sort, ?canonical) walking SortAlias facts; (c) unify_type(?a, ?b) orchestrating structural match + alias resolution + subtyping. The Rust unify_types (typing.rs:1131) stays as the operational fast path used by type_check. Note: Type values are already plain Term::Fn and unify structurally via SLD — the original 'Sort is opaque' framing was inaccurate. The unused sort_as_term/term_as_sort/can_be_sort stubs in reflect.anthill:136-140 should be removed as cleanup.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-011",
  description: "Typing as rules: express the typing pass as anthill rules (not just operations) using type_of(?env, ?occ, ?type) 3-arg relation. TypingEnv as data sort with constructors (empty, bind). Requires: (1) Sort in unifications (WI-010), (2) forward chaining or materialization to persist derived TypeOf facts, (3) tabling/memoization for recursive derivations. See Proposal 022 and 011 discussion. CLOSED 2026-04-23 (decision verified, scope abandoned): the original premises are addressed without needing the Horn-rules lift. (a) Sort participation in unification is implemented — types are plain Term::Fn and unify structurally via SLD; rust unify_types (typing.rs:1131) is the operational helper. (b) Typing logic is already expressed in anthill code via typing_pass_spec.anthill (operations-form spec, not Horn-rule form, but serving the same documentation/specification purpose). (c) Forward chaining and tabling infrastructure is significant work with no current consumer — better added when a real use case appears. Followup: WI-079 covers parity-testing between the operations-form spec and the Rust implementation. Do not reopen without a concrete use case for the Horn-rules form specifically.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-010"],
  status: Verified(at: "2026-04-23T00:00:00Z"))
