fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-173",
  description: "Surface pretty-printing for type expressions in `persistence/print.rs`. Today TermPrinter falls through to the generic `name(arg: val, ...)` Fn form for type terms — `arrow(param: …, result: …, effects: cons(...))` instead of `(A) -> B @ {E1, E2}`. Round-trip from KB → text → parse is therefore lossy/ugly for any operation signature, fact field referencing a type, or codegen output. Add per-shape handlers in `write_term`: (1) `arrow(param, result, effects)` → `(<param>) -> <result>` plus `@ <e>` for single effect or `@ {<e1>, <e2>, …}` for set; emit nothing when effects is `nil`. (2) `named_tuple(fields: List[TypeField])` → `(<f1>, <f2>, …)` where TypeField positional `_N` names print as bare types and named fields print as `n: T`. Arrow case detects when `param` is already a named_tuple and uses its parenthesised form directly to avoid double-wrap. (3) `sort_ref(name: Ref(S))` → bare `S`. (4) `parameterized(base, bindings: List[TypeBinding])` → `<base>[<k1> = <v1>, <k2> = <v2>]`. (5) `TypeBinding(name: Ref(K), type: T)` → `K = T`. Recursion goes through `write_term` so each handler's children re-enter and pick up the same surface form. Shared helper `walk_cons_list(tid) -> Vec<TermId>` for the list traversals. Tests in `persistence_test.rs` round-trip the canonical cases plus the multi-effect set (mirroring `load_arrow_type_with_effect_set_preserves_list` already in parse_test.rs). Driver: `(A) -> B @ {Modifies[host], Reads[host]}` should print as itself, not as the cons-list functor blob. Out of scope: `arrow_effect`-positional-form (used only by `build_instantiation_term` for sort instantiation contexts), tuple_type (no Fn shape used for it today).",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)
fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-174",
  description: "Replace dependents-count ordering in 'anthill-todo list' with chronological+topological mixed ordering. Today run_list (anthill-todo/src/main.rs:522-616) splits items into ready/blocked, sorts ready by transitive dependents count (most-unblocking first), and sorts blocked by id. Behavior to deliver: walk filtered items in chronological order (by id, since WI-NNN is sequential); for each item X not yet emitted, recursively emit X's still-unemitted dependencies first (topological/postorder), then X. Result is one global sequence where (a) each item appears after all its dependencies, and (b) the top-level cursor advances through items in chronological order, so the earliest WI anchors a topologically-ordered cluster of its deps just before it. Concretely: replace the count_transitive-sorting block with a postorder DFS over a chronologically-sorted item list, marking emitted to avoid duplicates and to short-circuit shared deps. Keep the ready-vs-blocked split (and the blocked section labelling) only if it still adds value — preferred shape is one merged list with [blocked] tags inline. Open question to resolve in the WI: whether closed (Delivered/Verified) deps should be skipped from the emitted list (probably yes — they're satisfied and don't need re-display) or shown as anchors. Acceptance: cargo-test green; eyeball-check 'anthill-todo list' output on the current ~65 open items shows the earliest open item appearing near the top with its open deps clustered immediately before it.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
  status: Open)

fact Feedback(content: "Status grouping: keep the existing top-level grouping by status — Open first, then Claimed, then Delivered (Verified hidden by default like today). Within each status group, apply the chronological+topological ordering described above. So the output shape is: [Open group: chrono-walk with deps clustered] then [Claimed group: same] then [Delivered group: same].", at: "2026-05-04T10:49:34Z", workitem: "WI-174", author: "user")
fact Feedback(content: "Keep the existing 'blocked' group as today: items with unmet deps go under a separate '-- blocked --' section. Apply chrono+topo ordering within both the ready section and the blocked section. So combined with status grouping: Open(ready: chrono+topo) / Open(blocked: chrono+topo) / Claimed(...) / Delivered(...).", at: "2026-05-04T10:50:04Z", workitem: "WI-174", author: "user")
fact Feedback(content: "Already implemented in resolve.rs (verified 2026-05-04). Lazy walk lives at step_init lines 358-374 with the [WI-030] tag: σ is applied to goals[0] only at selection time, memoized back into goals[0]; skipped when subst is empty. The corresponding eager apply_subst_each calls were dropped from step_choice_point (see [WI-030] comments at :1077 and :1109). A lazy_walk_calls stats counter and test assertion at :4595 verify the lazy walk is exercised; comment at :4601 records that the historical apply_subst_each_goals metric scaled n²/2 before the change.", at: "2026-05-04T19:55:12Z", workitem: "WI-030", author: "user")
fact Feedback(content: "Implemented as context-aware desugaring (proposal 019 §typing process). Replaced the unconditional 'ListLiteral → cons/nil' rewrite at load.rs:2889-2908 with one keyed on the surrounding entity field type. Touch points: rustland/anthill-core/src/kb/load.rs (convert_term gains a convert_term_with_expected wrapper that propagates Option<TermId> hints; named/positional args now carry the entity field's declared type into the recursive walk via entity_field_types) and rustland/anthill-core/src/kb/typing.rs (extract_type_param made pub(crate) for reuse). New helper find_list_element_type returns Option<Option<TermId>>: outer Some signals 'desugar here', inner Option carries the element type. Recurses through wrappers (Option[T = List[T = X]]) so the existing implicit-some convention in stage0 facts (e.g. depends_on: Option[T = List[T = String]] written as []) still desugars. Reuses kb::typing::list_to_vec / get_named_arg / extract_type_param rather than re-implementing cons walks. Bare List, parameterized List[T = X], and Option-wrapped List all desugar; Set/Vec/non-list contexts leave ListLiteral as-is for the eval path (eval/eval.rs:629 already builds list values from ListLiteral natively). Tests: 939+ tests in anthill-core all green; github_todo_test (cons/nil patterns over depends_on Option[List]) and eval_m2_test::m2_list_literal_builds_cons_chain still pass; anthill-todo CLI roundtrip verified.", at: "2026-05-04T22:32:59Z", workitem: "WI-007", author: "user")
fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-175",
  description: "FileStore retract: actually modify files at flush time. Implementation: Store::retract gains a kb argument and buffers the canonical printed form of the rule head. At flush time, parse each affected file, drop fact blocks whose head canonicalizes to a buffered retract, then append persisted writes. Inter-fact text outside fact blocks (comments, blank lines) is preserved via byte-range tracking; comments inside a fact block are not preserved. Persist plus flush is idempotent. Tests added in anthill-core/tests/persistence_test.rs: retract_unknown_rule_is_noop, retract_drops_fact_block_from_disk, retract_then_persist_replaces_in_place, retract_preserves_inter_fact_text, flush_is_idempotent_after_retract. Design: examples/github-todo/docs/anthill-migration.md section 5.1.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: [],
